Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the grated garlic, @roasted spice and herb blend{},
@panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{¼%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs,
then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Shape into mini sausage shapes, 4 per person. Flatten to make koftas.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the remaining @garlic clove{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{}
with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, scrunch to enclose it.

Arrange the koftas onto one side of a large baking tray. Place the garlic
parcel on the other side of the tray.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until the koftas are browned on
the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks.

In a medium bowl, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{½%tsp} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
stir through the tomatoes, then set aside.

Once the roasted garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it
out of the skin and mash with a fork.

In a small bowl, combine the roasted garlic and @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir well.

When everything's nearly ready, add the @red pepper chilli jelly{25%g},
@smoked paprika{1%tsp} and the @butter{10%g} to a large #frying pan{} on medium
heat.

Warm through to melt the butter, ~{1%minute}. Stir well to combine.

Add the koftas to the frying pan and stir to coat. Cook until piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

When you're almost ready to serve, toss the @baby leaf mix{20%g} with the
tomatoes.

To serve, spoon the yoghurt onto one side of each #plate{} and top with the
beef koftas. Spoon over the remaining butter sauce from the frying pan.

Serve with the chips and salad on the side. Enjoy!